      "message": "This seems we\u0027re shoehorning an IPMI concept into the (management-interface-independent) network configuration with this change. An ethernet interface itself has no concept of the LAN Alert mechanism specified by IPMI.\n\nDo we have a more appropriate object to host this? The channel definitions within the IPMI-specific code may be a more suitable.\n\nI understand that this may be the first of a series of changes to implement LAN alerts, but seems poorly sequenced; we can only validly indicate support for 0 destinations without the full alert capability defined. Do you have an implementation planned? I don\u0027t see any design docs for alerting at present.\n\nOn a naming item: you have used `NumofDestination` everywhere; capitalistion-wise, this should be `NumOfDestination`. However, in the scope of an ethernet interface, this doesn\u0027t specify enough context. Perhaps `SupportedAlertChannels` ?",
      "revId": "001148e6cd43bc752e6144032356807b8188d754",
